WEBVTT

00:06.308 --> 00:08.096
VERSACE: I've arranged an interview.

00:08.144 --> 00:09.344
DONATELLA: With who?

00:09.492 --> 00:11.081
With The Advocate magazine.

00:11.692 --> 00:13.416
The American publication.

00:14.659 --> 00:15.807
For gay readers.

00:16.628 --> 00:17.807
To say what?

00:18.694 --> 00:20.050
VERSACE: I've never said it.

00:20.295 --> 00:21.612
I'm gay.

00:22.589 --> 00:24.917
- To print? To publish?
- Yes.

00:29.738 --> 00:32.167
I handle publicity for this company.

00:32.345 --> 00:33.917
This is my responsibility.

00:33.942 --> 00:35.387
Yes, but this is not about you.

00:35.388 --> 00:36.937
And this is about more than you.

00:36.938 --> 00:37.964
In what way?

00:38.120 --> 00:40.440
The magazine has a modest circulation.

00:40.465 --> 00:42.537
How can you decide this
without consulting me?

00:42.538 --> 00:44.159
Uh, consulting you?

00:45.432 --> 00:47.042
Okay, I'm consulting you.

00:47.288 --> 00:48.537
What would you advise?

00:48.538 --> 00:50.188
ANTONIO: Yes, what would you advise?

00:51.854 --> 00:54.221
Ah, this is your idea.

00:54.688 --> 00:56.238
You want to be famous.

00:56.581 --> 00:59.137
Known around the world
as Versace's lover?

00:59.138 --> 01:01.729
For 13 years, I've been mistaken
for Gianni's assistant.

01:02.138 --> 01:04.437
And your pride is more
important than this company?

01:04.438 --> 01:05.637
ANTONIO: I've lived unseen.

01:05.638 --> 01:07.378
In great comfort, that's for sure.

01:07.403 --> 01:08.637
I never imagined

01:08.638 --> 01:09.987
being publicly acknowledged.

01:09.988 --> 01:12.651
I know my place, unlike you.

01:14.987 --> 01:16.163
And what is my place?

01:16.188 --> 01:19.187
- (POUNDS TABLE)
- Enough! Enough, both of you.

01:19.188 --> 01:21.837
I will not... fight over this.

01:21.838 --> 01:24.659
It was my idea, it was my idea.

01:25.188 --> 01:26.925
Donatella, walk with me.

01:27.188 --> 01:28.276
Come.

01:39.479 --> 01:40.854
I want you to support me.

01:41.229 --> 01:42.393
You know that.

01:43.192 --> 01:45.956
All these people's lives depend on you.

01:46.800 --> 01:49.510
We're opening stores in
countries where it is illegal.

01:49.667 --> 01:51.385
Where it is a crime.

01:51.888 --> 01:53.487
You have to visit those countries.

01:53.488 --> 01:54.937
They might refuse your entry,

01:54.938 --> 01:57.388
refuse a visa, refuse to
do business with you.

01:59.111 --> 02:01.862
Tell me, honestly...

02:03.948 --> 02:05.510
what do you think could happen?

02:05.679 --> 02:06.776
(SCOFFS)

02:07.464 --> 02:09.687
The rock stars, the actors,

02:09.687 --> 02:12.229
the royalty whose
endorsements we cherish...

02:13.417 --> 02:15.888
they might not want to be
associated with us.

02:17.440 --> 02:19.409
Well, at least we keep Elton, no?

02:21.388 --> 02:22.688
You joke?

02:22.831 --> 02:23.925
Joke?

02:24.138 --> 02:26.637
We're talking about the
survival of the company.

02:26.638 --> 02:28.010
Is that what you believe?

02:29.635 --> 02:31.589
You live in isolation.

02:31.734 --> 02:34.234
Surrounded by beauty and kindness.

02:34.688 --> 02:37.034
You have forgotten
how ugly the world can be.

02:39.096 --> 02:40.565
The women we design for,

02:41.464 --> 02:42.768
they're strong, yes?

02:42.972 --> 02:44.221
They're fearless.

02:44.222 --> 02:45.229
They're not ashamed.

02:45.254 --> 02:47.362
- This is not the same.
- It's not the same.

02:47.656 --> 02:49.971
Is the brand of Versace
braver than the man?

02:56.794 --> 02:59.034
Are you angry with me or with the world?

03:02.721 --> 03:06.121
When we list the company
on the New York Stock Exchange,

03:06.122 --> 03:07.995
what will your admission cost?

03:08.042 --> 03:10.354
$1 million? $100 million?

03:10.872 --> 03:13.322
Or will it make this
company worth nothing?

03:14.697 --> 03:16.831
You're exaggerating.
Don't be ridiculous.

03:19.728 --> 03:21.120
Perry Ellis.

03:21.941 --> 03:24.991
When he walked onto the
runway dying of AIDS,

03:25.055 --> 03:28.823
so weak, his assistants
caught him when he took a bow...

03:31.037 --> 03:33.971
- Perhaps his most important show.
- After that,

03:33.996 --> 03:36.446
- people stopped buying his clothes.
- Some people.

03:36.479 --> 03:38.558
- No, Gianni, a lot of people.
- No, no, no. Some people.

03:38.582 --> 03:39.832
Some people.

03:43.293 --> 03:45.221
ANSWER ME THIS: why now?

03:47.289 --> 03:48.550
Because I was sick.

03:50.507 --> 03:51.675
And I didn't die.

03:54.422 --> 03:55.862
I have a second chance.

03:57.573 --> 03:59.182
It's a miracle that I'm alive.

04:01.425 --> 04:03.510
And yet I ask myself every day,

04:03.535 --> 04:05.690
what have I done to deserve this?

04:08.503 --> 04:09.753
Why am I still here?

04:10.365 --> 04:11.573
To be afraid?

04:13.338 --> 04:14.346
No.

04:14.385 --> 04:16.772
I'm alive and I must use it.

04:18.401 --> 04:21.909
synced and corrected by susinz
*www.addic7ed.com*

04:40.530 --> 04:42.257
AMERICAN EXPRESS OPERATOR:
Mr. Cunanan, I appreciate

04:42.281 --> 04:44.459
that your credit history
used to be impeccable...

04:44.484 --> 04:48.184
ANDREW: All I need to do
is make one more purchase,

04:48.771 --> 04:50.834
and that's for a one-way ticket
to Minneapolis

04:50.859 --> 04:51.943
on Northwest Airlines.

04:51.968 --> 04:54.771
OPERATOR: Sir, American Express is
not in the business of loaning...

04:54.796 --> 04:56.819
Well, once I get to Minneapolis,
I can fix everything.

04:56.843 --> 04:59.505
Then I will be your very
best customer again,

04:59.530 --> 05:01.052
- I promise you.
- OPERATOR: I don't know

05:01.076 --> 05:03.228
- what's in Minneapolis.
- My two best friends.

05:03.405 --> 05:04.671
I'm moving in with my friend David,

05:04.695 --> 05:06.770
and Jeff actually owes me
more than $10,000.

05:06.795 --> 05:08.805
But once I get that money,
they're gonna help me

05:08.855 --> 05:11.104
turn my life right back around.

05:11.105 --> 05:12.854
OPERATOR:
Will you be making a repayment?

05:12.855 --> 05:16.104
Well, yes, once I get to Minneapolis.

05:16.105 --> 05:17.804
OPERATOR: Mr. Cunanan, to be clear,

05:17.805 --> 05:19.454
you're requesting that American Express

05:19.455 --> 05:21.304
extend your credit
to cover a one-way ticket

05:21.305 --> 05:23.604
in order to make a repayment, correct?

05:23.605 --> 05:25.454
Yes, that's all I need.

05:25.748 --> 05:28.006
OPERATOR: (SIGHS)
Let me talk to my supervisor.

05:28.070 --> 05:29.271
I can hold.

05:29.570 --> 05:31.139
(HOLD MUSIC PLAYS OVER PHONE)

05:31.805 --> 05:33.029
♪

06:02.468 --> 06:03.662
♪

06:22.742 --> 06:24.170
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

06:41.164 --> 06:42.248
May I?

06:45.530 --> 06:46.701
(MAN SIGHS)

06:49.781 --> 06:50.928
You serve?

06:52.413 --> 06:53.545
Yes, sir.

06:54.014 --> 06:55.357
- Marines?
- Navy.

06:56.576 --> 06:58.193
I was on board the USS Gridley.

06:58.286 --> 07:00.303
1st Infantry Division. Gulf War.

07:01.631 --> 07:03.935
- Jeff.
- Samson.

07:05.123 --> 07:06.622
Where was the Gridley?

07:06.905 --> 07:08.326
Persian Gulf in '92.

07:09.029 --> 07:11.123
After that, we were docked in San Diego.

07:11.305 --> 07:14.185
They were refitting her,
but they changed their minds

07:14.210 --> 07:15.889
and decided to decommission her.

07:16.807 --> 07:18.656
Still makes me sad. She was a good ship.

07:20.404 --> 07:21.605
You miss it?

07:21.655 --> 07:23.154
(CHUCKLES)

07:23.326 --> 07:24.545
Every day.

07:25.558 --> 07:26.826
Why'd you leave?

07:28.205 --> 07:29.310
I don't know.

07:31.560 --> 07:33.014
I regret it, for sure.

07:34.205 --> 07:35.854
SAMSON: Well, I was never gonna
become an officer,

07:35.855 --> 07:37.535
- so I figured...
- JEFF: I was an officer.

07:38.732 --> 07:40.810
- You were?
- Graduate from Annapolis.

07:42.160 --> 07:45.037
My brother's a navy corpsman,
my sister's in the air force.

07:46.732 --> 07:47.850
You married?

07:48.342 --> 07:49.420
No.

07:50.826 --> 07:52.475
Waiting for the right one, I guess.

07:53.475 --> 07:54.623
Why'd you leave?

07:56.045 --> 07:58.148
I haven't heard of many officers leaving

07:58.462 --> 07:59.881
to work at a place like this.

08:02.467 --> 08:05.076
- This place is okay.
- Sure, it's okay.

08:06.036 --> 08:07.576
For a man who went to Annapolis?

08:09.155 --> 08:10.553
I made the decision.

08:11.451 --> 08:12.498
SAMSON: Right.

08:13.193 --> 08:14.980
My wife always says
I ask too many questions.

08:15.005 --> 08:17.053
I made the decision, okay?

08:17.555 --> 08:19.604
I offended you. I'm sorry.

08:20.355 --> 08:21.921
- Why don't we leave it there?
- (SLAMS TABLE LOUDLY)

08:21.945 --> 08:23.530
JEFF: I made the decision!

08:40.434 --> 08:41.600
SAMSON: Jeff.

08:45.332 --> 08:46.498
Jeff.

08:47.841 --> 08:50.631
Someone named Andrew called,
left a message.

08:51.148 --> 08:52.771
Says he'll see you at the airport.

09:00.105 --> 09:02.155
(WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY OVER P.A.)

09:10.592 --> 09:12.959
- Hey.
- Didn't think you were gonna show.

09:13.490 --> 09:14.732
I didn't think so, either.

09:15.287 --> 09:16.842
Do you know why he's coming here?

09:16.867 --> 09:19.178
- Nope.
- I don't get it.

09:19.443 --> 09:21.146
Nothing's happening this weekend.

09:21.232 --> 09:23.412
He's got no one. He's got nothing.

09:23.437 --> 09:25.804
Everything he's told you
about his life's a lie.

09:25.873 --> 09:27.014
You know that, right?

09:27.274 --> 09:28.584
Do you even like him?

09:31.006 --> 09:32.420
He was there for me once.

09:32.445 --> 09:34.146
I owe him. It's not the same.

09:35.361 --> 09:37.510
- I feel kind of sorry for him.
- Don't.

09:37.748 --> 09:39.685
- He's lonely.
- For a reason.

09:40.655 --> 09:42.835
Look, I'm gonna give him this
weekend, for old times' sake,

09:42.859 --> 09:44.123
and then I'm done with him.

09:44.198 --> 09:45.889
He's here for three nights.

09:46.709 --> 09:48.254
He can have my apartment tomorrow night.

09:48.255 --> 09:49.537
I'll stay at my sister's.

09:49.562 --> 09:51.521
But don't tell him where I am, okay?

09:52.006 --> 09:53.615
He's so crazy, he might just show up.

09:53.640 --> 09:55.795
ANDREW: The Three Amigos!

09:56.904 --> 09:58.256
- Hi.
- How are you?

09:58.281 --> 10:00.310
Oh, good. Good.

10:00.335 --> 10:01.896
- Jeff.
- Andrew.

10:03.584 --> 10:05.982
Oh, we're gonna have
so much fun this weekend.

10:06.379 --> 10:08.279
It's gonna be just like old times.

10:08.304 --> 10:09.662
Not like old times.

10:09.935 --> 10:11.084
Why would you say that?

10:11.265 --> 10:13.466
I'm not gonna be able to
hang out with you guys tonight.

10:13.545 --> 10:14.795
Oh, why not?

10:15.426 --> 10:17.225
Aside from everything you've done?

10:18.154 --> 10:19.342
What did I do?

10:19.865 --> 10:21.279
My company has a sales conference.

10:21.304 --> 10:22.592
I'm away till Sunday.

10:23.035 --> 10:24.834
But I'll be sure
to write you a postcard.

10:25.467 --> 10:28.404
Oh, are you still annoyed about that?

10:28.405 --> 10:29.954
I thought we talked about this.
I expla...

10:29.955 --> 10:32.607
I accidentally sent
Jeff's dad a postcard.

10:32.632 --> 10:35.764
I put "Stan Trail"
instead of "Jeff Trail."

10:35.789 --> 10:37.217
And they don't know that he's gay,

10:37.242 --> 10:39.873
and I signed it "Love, Drew. Kiss-kiss."

10:40.201 --> 10:42.326
I made a mistake. I'm sorry.

10:43.107 --> 10:44.287
So what?

10:44.998 --> 10:46.304
You can stay at my place tomorrow night.

10:46.305 --> 10:47.554
I won't be at home.

10:47.555 --> 10:49.209
Why do I need a place to stay?

10:50.084 --> 10:51.451
I'm busy tomorrow night.

10:52.017 --> 10:53.263
Doing what?

10:53.833 --> 10:55.021
Seeing a friend.

10:56.967 --> 10:58.225
Who? What friend?

10:59.173 --> 11:00.639
No one you know.

11:03.305 --> 11:05.305
(MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY OVER P.A.)

11:12.228 --> 11:14.607
Hey, buddy. Hey.

11:14.955 --> 11:16.600
Hey, hey.

11:17.070 --> 11:20.969
Hey, you. Hey. How was your day?

11:21.201 --> 11:22.854
How was your day?

11:22.855 --> 11:23.975
Hey, hey.

11:24.000 --> 11:25.318
You miss me?

11:28.115 --> 11:29.193
What's this?

11:29.378 --> 11:30.592
I got you something.

11:38.039 --> 11:39.264
Open it.

11:41.320 --> 11:42.514
Open it.

11:59.386 --> 12:00.529
(DAVID SCOFFS)

12:04.198 --> 12:05.318
David?

12:07.075 --> 12:08.170
David.

12:08.803 --> 12:09.982
Listen to me.

12:11.623 --> 12:14.654
David Madson, you are the man
that I want to spend

12:14.655 --> 12:16.100
the rest of my life with.

12:18.521 --> 12:19.779
Will you marry me?

12:19.804 --> 12:20.780
Andrew!

12:20.805 --> 12:22.331
You don't have to give
me an answer right now.

12:22.355 --> 12:23.741
You can think about it
for the next few days.

12:23.765 --> 12:25.459
- We can't get married.
- Why not?

12:25.484 --> 12:27.021
It's against the law.

12:27.046 --> 12:29.475
- Who cares about that?
- Everyone.

12:30.644 --> 12:32.529
Well, I don't.

12:34.568 --> 12:37.201
It-it can't be done. It's insane.

12:37.226 --> 12:39.880
Okay, okay.
We'll call it something else.

12:39.905 --> 12:41.646
We'll call it, um... We'll call it, uh,

12:41.671 --> 12:43.373
a-a commitment ceremony.

12:44.193 --> 12:45.178
What?

12:45.203 --> 12:47.748
No. No, it-it's not...

12:49.205 --> 12:50.412
the term...

12:52.562 --> 12:53.748
Then what is it?

12:56.221 --> 12:58.053
The idea of you and me.

13:01.989 --> 13:03.154
Think about it.

13:03.555 --> 13:04.858
Think about it for the next few days.

13:04.882 --> 13:05.991
Think about it over the weekend,

13:06.015 --> 13:10.146
and if, for whatever
reason, it's-it's a no,

13:10.171 --> 13:13.060
then you can keep the watch, regardless.

13:13.814 --> 13:14.850
For what?

13:15.909 --> 13:17.076
For what?

13:18.805 --> 13:21.225
F-For-for turning my life around.

13:24.115 --> 13:25.350
I got a new job.

13:25.943 --> 13:28.162
I got a new condo in San Francisco.

13:28.381 --> 13:29.830
I'm a whole new person.

13:30.292 --> 13:32.998
A-And a-all I need is...

13:33.889 --> 13:37.162
is someone to be a new person for.

13:46.005 --> 13:48.005
(INSECTS CHIRPING, DOGS BARKING)

13:58.396 --> 13:59.481
Give it to me.

13:59.506 --> 14:00.779
- (SIGHS)
- Here.

14:01.105 --> 14:02.443
I don't want to be any trouble.

14:02.468 --> 14:04.318
No trouble. I love that you're here.

14:04.533 --> 14:05.709
Why are you here?

14:07.193 --> 14:08.537
I'm avoiding Andrew.

14:09.155 --> 14:11.795
The guy that sent Dad
the postcard, trying to out you?

14:12.279 --> 14:13.954
He claims it was a mistake.

14:14.240 --> 14:15.654
I've made a lot of mistakes in my life.

14:15.655 --> 14:17.053
Never sent a postcard by mistake.

14:17.078 --> 14:19.193
You've never made any
mistakes in your life.

14:19.497 --> 14:20.387
No.

14:20.412 --> 14:21.779
- I know.
- (CHUCKLES)

14:22.920 --> 14:24.412
I'm not gonna hang out with him.

14:25.646 --> 14:28.014
You shouldn't let him have
that kind of control over you.

14:28.412 --> 14:30.678
He was threatening you
with that postcard.

14:31.271 --> 14:33.326
Why don't you just tell
Mom and Dad you're gay?

14:33.467 --> 14:35.240
(SIGHS) I know what they're gonna think.

14:35.265 --> 14:37.764
- They love you.
- It's not the right time.

14:37.881 --> 14:38.980
It's never the right time.

14:38.981 --> 14:40.420
I don't want to ruin this.

14:40.523 --> 14:42.084
Ruin what? Childbirth?

14:42.109 --> 14:43.154
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

14:43.340 --> 14:45.865
They're gonna be so happy. I...

14:47.576 --> 14:49.998
I want you to do it, and it's my baby,

14:50.023 --> 14:53.060
so I'm ordering you, as your
superior officer: tell them.

14:53.713 --> 14:54.935
Let me think about it.

14:55.352 --> 14:56.851
You've thought about it enough.

14:56.953 --> 14:58.178
(LAUGHS SOFTLY)

14:59.387 --> 15:00.678
That's for sure.

15:00.703 --> 15:01.857
(SIGHS)

15:05.553 --> 15:09.693
I'm looking forward
to being an uncle so much.

15:14.081 --> 15:15.475
(POLKA MUSIC PLAYING)

15:18.839 --> 15:20.988
ANDREW: Never been
to a polka club before.

15:21.342 --> 15:23.230
Such a great idea, it's so original.

15:23.231 --> 15:24.240
Ooh, I like this.

15:24.265 --> 15:25.810
This... this-this feels special.

15:25.835 --> 15:27.034
It's memorable.

15:27.268 --> 15:28.748
It wasn't my choice.

15:28.918 --> 15:29.918
What do you mean?

15:30.087 --> 15:31.514
I'm waiting for my friend.

15:31.959 --> 15:33.586
She has quirky taste.

15:34.467 --> 15:35.584
What friend?

15:35.609 --> 15:36.701
Uh, Linda.

15:37.177 --> 15:38.342
I work with her.

15:39.146 --> 15:41.037
Oh, David.

15:41.062 --> 15:42.654
- Hi.
- (LAUGHING): Hi.

15:42.679 --> 15:43.928
- How are you?
- I'm good,

15:43.953 --> 15:45.107
- how are you?
- I'm good.

15:45.132 --> 15:47.092
Uh, Linda, this is my friend Andrew.

15:47.291 --> 15:48.340
- Hi.
- Friend? (CHUCKLES)

15:48.826 --> 15:50.139
I'm more than a friend.

15:51.926 --> 15:53.428
Wow. You got him that?

15:53.644 --> 15:55.545
Just to show how much he means to me.

15:55.684 --> 15:57.553
It's worth $10,000.

15:58.492 --> 15:59.584
Wow.

16:03.140 --> 16:04.803
("TICK TOCK POLKA" PLAYING)

16:28.619 --> 16:29.982
(POLKA MUSIC FADING)

16:38.281 --> 16:41.506
♪ Tick, tick, tick, tock
goes the clock on the wall ♪

16:41.531 --> 16:45.162
♪ As we're dancing
the evening away ♪

16:46.575 --> 16:47.818
♪ Tick, tick, tick, tock... ♪

16:47.843 --> 16:49.343
LINDA: So, what do you do?

16:51.541 --> 16:52.896
I make movie sets.

16:53.831 --> 16:56.170
Right now I'm building the sets
for the Titanic movie,

16:56.195 --> 16:57.195
in Mexico.

16:57.589 --> 16:59.154
And you're here for David?

17:00.865 --> 17:02.451
There's no one I love more.

17:02.994 --> 17:04.217
He's a great guy.

17:05.500 --> 17:09.170
Um, we were just talking
about movie sets and Mexico.

17:10.381 --> 17:11.529
Mexico?

17:11.554 --> 17:12.654
Let's go dance.

17:14.281 --> 17:15.482
Andrew.

17:21.310 --> 17:23.474
I don't need the whole weekend
to think about it.

17:23.759 --> 17:25.217
I-I can't hear you.

17:25.242 --> 17:26.560
The music's too loud.

17:26.585 --> 17:28.780
I don't need the whole weekend
to think about it.

17:28.781 --> 17:30.607
I can't hear you, let's just dance.

17:30.632 --> 17:32.092
We can't get married.

17:32.806 --> 17:33.967
We can't.

17:35.139 --> 17:37.725
You understand? I mean,
even if we could, we can't.

17:41.389 --> 17:42.926
I don't know what else to say.

17:42.951 --> 17:44.975
I'm-I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.

